    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 offensive outlook for May 4, 2026, is headlined by **Josh Lowe** (70.92) and **Gunnar Henderson** (68.83), who emerge as our premier starters. **Josh Lowe** benefits from a high-ceiling matchup against Davis Martin (4.38 xERA) with the added boost of favorable wind conditions, while **Gunnar Henderson** thrives in the leadoff spot against a suspect Schlittler. **Heliot Ramos** (67.76) also sits firmly in the \"Strong\" category; his leadoff role combined with a generous 4.91 xERA from Randy V\u00e1squez makes him a vital catalyst. We are also monitoring the wind-aided environments for **Sam Antonacci** and **Nolan Schanuel**, both of whom see their floor elevated by weather factors at the park today.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Dominic Smith**, who fell just short of the lineup with a score of 36.59. While he offered moderate platoon utility, the stiff challenge posed by Gilbert (3.04 xERA) ultimately suppressed his efficiency, leading us to favor the higher-upside profiles of our active starters. We remain thin in the middle infield due to the absences of **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, all of whom are currently navigating injuries or roster inactivity. \n\nInvestors should proceed with caution regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for several key players, specifically **Drake Baldwin**, **Sam Antonacci**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Josh Lowe**, **Nolan Schanuel**, and **Heliot Ramos**. Should any of these bats be relegated to the bench once official lineups are posted, the efficiency drop could necessitate a shift toward our deeper reserves. With **Jorge Polanco**, **Jacob Wilson**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Brady House** ready to slot in if needed, we have the depth to mitigate late-breaking lineup surprises while keeping our eyes on the high-speed profiles we prioritize for the scarce stolen base category.",
